\title{Deep Debug}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Multi-agent investigation for stubborn bugs. Triggers: going in circles debugging, complex bugs resisting normal debugging, symptoms don't match expectations, need parallel investigation, browser+API interaction bugs, deep investigation.}

\subtree{
\title{Deep Debug - Multi-Agent Investigation}
\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\ul{
\li{Going in circles -- multiple fix attempts, nothing works}
\li{Browser + API interaction bugs -- need to see Network tab, console logs}
\li{Symptoms don't match expectations -- something deeper is wrong}
\li{Complex state management bugs -- React hooks, closures, race conditions}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{The Process}
\subtree{
\title{Phase 1: Gather Evidence (Before Hypothesizing)}
\p{\strong{For browser-related bugs}, use Chrome MCP tools:}

\pre{\startverb
mcp__claude-in-chrome__read_network_requests  // duplicates, failures, timing
mcp__claude-in-chrome__read_console_messages  // errors, warnings, debug output
mcp__claude-in-chrome__read_page              // page state
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{For backend bugs}, gather: error logs, stack traces, request/response payloads, database query logs, timing information.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 2: Launch Parallel Investigation (3 Agents)}
\subtree{
\title{Agent 1: Execution Tracer (debugger)}
\pre{\startverb
Task(subagent_type="debugger", prompt="""
EVIDENCE: [paste network/console evidence]

Trace the execution path that leads to this bug. Find:
1. Where the bug originates
2. What triggers it
3. The exact line/function causing the issue

Focus on TRACING, not guessing.
""")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Agent 2: Pattern Analyzer (code-reviewer)}
\pre{\startverb
Task(subagent_type="code-reviewer", prompt="""
EVIDENCE: [paste evidence]

Review the relevant code for common bug patterns:
- React useCallback/useMemo dependency issues
- Stale closures
- Race conditions
- State update ordering
- Missing error handling

Find patterns that EXPLAIN the evidence.
""")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Agent 3: Entry Point Mapper (Explore)}
\pre{\startverb
Task(subagent_type="Explore", prompt="""
EVIDENCE: [paste evidence]

Map all entry points that could trigger this behavior:
- All places [function] is called
- All event handlers involved
- All state updates that affect this

Find if something is being called MULTIPLE TIMES or from UNEXPECTED places.
""")
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 3: Cross-Reference Findings}
\pre{\startverb
| Signal | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| All 3 agree on root cause | High confidence -- fix it |
| 2 agree, 1 different | Investigate the difference |
| All 3 different | Need more evidence |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 4: Verify Fix}
\p{Re-gather the same evidence to confirm: network tab shows expected behavior, console has no errors, state updates correctly.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Real Example: Duplicate API Calls Bug}
\p{\strong{Evidence}: Network tab showed 2 fetch requests for the same message.}

\pre{\startverb
| Agent | Finding |
|-------|---------|
| debugger | `state.messages` in useCallback deps causes callback recreation |
| code-reviewer | Same finding + explained React pattern causing it |
| Explore | Verified UI layer wasn't double-calling (ruled out) |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Root Cause}: \code{\startverb sendMessage\stopverb} useCallback had \code{\startverb state.messages\stopverb} in dependency array. Every state update recreated the callback, causing duplicate calls during re-renders.}

\p{\strong{Fix}:}

\pre{\startverb
const stateRef = useRef(state);
stateRef.current = state;

const sendMessage = useCallback(async (text) => {
  const messages = stateRef.current.messages;
  // ...
}, [/* state.messages removed */]);
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Bug Patterns}
\p{\strong{React Hook Issues}: state in useCallback dependencies, missing dependencies causing stale closures, useEffect running multiple times.}

\p{\strong{API/Network Issues}: duplicate requests, race conditions, CORS failures, timeout handling.}

\p{\strong{State Management Issues}: updates not batching correctly, optimistic updates conflicting with server response, multiple sources of truth.}
}
}